08/10/2007
REYKJAVIK, Iceland -- The NATO Parliamentary Assembly Defence Committee approved a draft resolution Sunday (October 7th) that encourages governments to invite Macedonia, Albania and Croatia to start accession negotiations at the Alliance's summit in Bucharest next April.
The resolution calls on national parliaments to demonstrate more commitment to ratify the necessary protocols for membership of the countries aspiring to join NATO.
The annual NATO Parliamentary Assembly session opened in Iceland's capital, Reykjavik, on Friday.
(Vecernji list - 08/10/07;
Makfax -A1, Javno.com, Telma TV - 07/10/07)
